617
00:37:13,773 --> 00:37:14,732
Judge Sim.

618
00:37:16,150 --> 00:37:20,071
Fine. I can't force her to do anything
if she doesn't want to.

619
00:37:20,154 --> 00:37:23,324
I've done my part, right?

620
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:27,787
I found her.
She's at the convalescent hospital.

621
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:29,413
Yes.

622
00:37:31,540 --> 00:37:32,500
Who was that?

623
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:36,545
Your friends you met when you went AWOL…
You're in a runaway gang with them, right?

624
00:37:36,629 --> 00:37:38,839
Yes, but I'm the victim here.

625
00:37:38,923 --> 00:37:40,424
Save it for the police.

626
00:37:40,508 --> 00:37:42,385
Then the phone call just now--

627
00:37:42,468 --> 00:37:44,971
The Juvenile Act, Section 4, Clause 1.

628
00:37:45,054 --> 00:37:47,473
"Juveniles who are prone
to committing criminal offenses

629
00:37:48,516 --> 00:37:50,726
will be taken into custody
as a status offender."

630
00:37:51,352 --> 00:37:54,230
-Judge Sim!
-Yes, I admit it.

631
00:37:55,231 --> 00:37:58,526
I thought I might have
taken it too far like you said.

632
00:37:58,609 --> 00:38:01,404
